<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--Rifleman     06-14 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Rifleman,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Camouflaged Man With War Games Toy Gun Apprehended At Department
Store</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CERRITOS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man wearing camouflage clothing and
carrying a gun that fires paint balls was arrested by a SWAT team
that shot out his car's tires in a department store parking lot,
authorities said.
   No one was injured.
   Passers-by who thought the gun was a high-powered rifle called
about 11:15 a.m. Monday to report Mark A. Lagana, 29, of Lakewood,
sitting in his car outside a Fedco store, Los Angeles County
sheriff's Deputy Richard Dinsmoor said.
   A special weapons team spent three hours watching Lagana, then
fired three shots into the rear tires of his car as he started to
drive it out of the parking space, Dinsmoor said.
   Lagana surrendered immediately and was held for psychiatric
evaluation, Dinsmoor said. The gun, of a type used in simulated
battles, was confiscated.
</TEXT>
