<1ST_LINE>u a BC-ExecutionsList 2Takes   06-14 1039</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Executions List, 2 Takes,1069</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>List of U.S. Executions Since 1976</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Byrne Execution, PM-Louisiana Execution, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of convicted killers executed since the U.S.
Supreme Court allowed states to restore the death penalty in 1976:
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1977</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   1. Gary Gilmore, 36, executed Jan. 17 by a firing squad in Utah
for the murder of a motel clerk.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1979</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   2. John Spenkelink, 30, electrocuted May 25 in Florida for
murdering a traveling companion.
   3. Jesse Bishop, 46, executed in Nevada's gas chamber Oct. 22
for murdering a newlywed.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1981</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   4. Steven Judy, 24, electrocuted March 9 in Indiana for killing
a woman and her three children.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1982</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   5. Frank Coppola, 38, electrocuted Aug. 10 in Virginia for
killing a housewife.
   6. Charlie Brooks Jr., 40, killed by injection Dec. 7 in Texas
for murdering a used-car salesman.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1983</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   7. John Evans III, 33, electrocuted April 22 in Alabama for
murdering a pawnbroker.
   8. Jimmy Lee Gray, 34, executed Sept. 2 in Mississippi's gas
chamber for murdering a 3-year-old girl.
   9. Robert Sullivan, 36, electrocuted Nov. 30 in Florida for the
shotgun slaying of a restaurant assistant manager.
   10. Robert Wayne Williams, 31, electrocuted Dec. 14 in Louisiana
for the killing of a supermarket guard during a holdup.
   11. John Eldon Smith, 53, electrocuted Dec. 15 in Georgia for
murdering two newlyweds.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1984</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   12. Anthony Antone, 66, electrocuted Jan. 26 in Florida for
arranging the murder of a private eye.
   13. Johnny Taylor Jr., 30, electrocuted Feb. 29 in Louisiana for
stabbing a man to death in the New Orleans suburb of Kenner.
   14. James David Autry, 29, executed by injection March 14 in
Texas for the shooting death a convenience store clerk.
   15. James W. Hutchins, 54, executed by injection March 16 in
North Carolina for killing two sheriff's deputies.
   16. Ronald Clark O'Bryan, 39, executed by injection March 31 in
Texas for killing his 8-year-old son with cyanide-laced Halloween
candy.
   17. Elmo Patrick Sonnier, 35, electrocuted April 5 in Louisiana
for killing two teen-agers near New Iberia in 1977.
   18. Arthur F. Goode III, 30, electrocuted April 5 in Florida for
killing a 9-year-old boy.
   19. James Adams, 47, electrocuted May 10 in Florida for killing
a millionaire rancher.
   20. Carl Shriner, 30, electrocuted June 20 in Florida for
killing a convenience store clerk.
   21. Ivon R. Stanley, 28, electrocuted July 12 in Georgia for
killing an insurance salesman who was robbed, beaten, shot and
buried alive.
   22. David L. Washington, 34, electrocuted July 13 in Florida for
three murders in eight days in 1976.
   23. Ernest John Dobbert Jr., 46, electrocuted Sept. 7 in Florida
for the 1971 killing of his 9-year-old daughter.
   24. Timothy Baldwin, 46, electrocuted Sept. 10 in Louisiana for
the 1978 killing of an 81-year-old woman who was beaten during a
robbery in her home.
   25. James Henry, 34, electrocuted Sept. 20 in Florida for
killing an elderly leader of Orlando's black community in a 1974
robbery.
   26. Linwood Briley, 30, electrocuted Oct. 13 in Virginia for the
robbery and murder of a Richmond disc jockey.
   27. Earnest Knighton Jr., 38, electrocuted Oct. 30 in Louisiana
for killing a service station owner.
   28. Thomas Andy Barefoot, 39, executed by injection Oct. 30 in
Texas for killing a policeman.
   29. Velma Barfield, 52, executed by injection Nov. 2 in North
Carolina for poisoning her boyfriend.
   30. Timothy Palmes, 37, electrocuted Nov. 8 in Florida for
killing a store owner whose body was placed in a box and dumped in
a river.
   31. Alpha Otis Stephens, 39, electrocuted Dec. 12 in Georgia for
killing a contractor who had interrupted a burglary.
   32. Robert Lee Willie, 26, electrocuted Dec. 28 in Louisiana for
raping and murdering an 18-year-old Mandeville woman.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1985</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   33. David Dene Martin, 32, electrocuted Jan. 4 in Louisiana for
murdering his wife's lover and three other people.
   34. Roosevelt Green, 28, electrocuted Jan. 9 in Georgia for
killing a convenience store clerk.
   35. Joseph Carl Shaw, 29, electrocuted Jan. 11 in South Carolina
for murdering a teen-age boy and a teen-age girl and raping the
girl.
   36. Doyle Skillern, 48, executed by injection Jan. 16 for being
an accomplice in the 1974 slaying of an undercover Texas narcotics
agent.
   37. James David Raulerson, 33, electrocuted Jan. 30 in Florida
for killing a Jacksonville policeman in a restaurant robbery in
1975.
   38. Van Roosevelt Solomon, 42, electrocuted Feb. 20 in Georgia
for killing a convenience store operator.
   39. Johnny Paul Witt, 42, electrocuted March 6 in Florida for
killing an 11-year-old boy and then sexually abusing and mutilating
the body.
   40. Stephen Peter Morin, 37, executed by injection March 13 in
Texas for killing a 21-year-old woman.
   41. John C. Young, 28, electrocuted March 20 in Georgia for
fatally beating three elderly people in Macon in 1974.
   42. James D. Briley, 28, electrocuted April 18 in Virginia for
killing a pregnant woman and her 5-year-old son.
   43. Jesse de la Rosa, 23, executed in Texas by injection May 15
for murdering a convenience store clerk in 1979.
   44. Marvin Francois, 39, electrocuted in Florida May 29 for
killing six people during the robbery of a ``drug house'' in 1977.
   45. Charles Milton, 34, executed by injection in Texas on June
25 for killing a liquor store owner during an aborted robbery in
1977.
   46. Morris Odell Mason, 32, executed in Virginia's electric
chair June 25 for raping and murdering an elderly woman, nailing
her hand to a chair and then setting her house on fire in 1978
during a crime spree.
   47. Henry Martinez Porter, 43, executed by injection in Texas on
July 9 for killing a policeman.
   48. Charles Rumbaugh, 28, executed by injection in Texas on
Sept. 11 for murdering a jeweler when he was 17 years old. It was
the first execution in more than two decades for a crime committed
by someone under age 18.
   49. William E. Vandiver, 37, electrocuted in Indiana on Oct. 16
for stabbing and dismembering his father-in-law.
   50. Carroll Edward Cole, 47, executed by injection in Nevada on
Dec. 6 for one of at least a dozen women he admitted killing for
revenge against his abusive mother.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>MORE</NOTE>
</DOC>
