<HEAD>Babbitt: Southerner Needed on Democratic Presidential Ticket</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former presidential candidate Bruce Babbitt
said Democratic presidential nominee-apparent Michael Dukakis
should nominate a ``generic Southerner'' as his running mate.
   Speaking with reporters on Monday, Babbitt said he
``absolutely'' planned to campaign on behalf of the Massachusetts
governor this fall, hoping to press specifically for environmental
issues.
   He offered some unsolicited advice to the Democratic
presidential nominee-to-be, saying Dukakis should pick a southern
running mate. He kiddingly placed himself in that column.
   ``Which Southerner? Well, I once said to him, I'm from southern
Arizona,'' Babbitt joked.
