<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Soviet-NukeTest     06-14 0114</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Soviet-Nuke Test,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soviets Explode 20 Kiloton Bomb Underground</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union conducted an underground nuclear
test today on the steppes of Central Asia, the Tass news agency
said.
   In a two-sentence report, the agency said the blast had a yield
of 20 kilotons and was carried out ``for the purpose of upgrading
military technology.''
   The test was staged at the Semipalatinsk range in the Central
Asian republic of Kazakhstan, Tass said. It provided no further
details.
   Twenty kilotons, the equivalent of 20,000 tons of TNT, was the
force of the U.S. atom bomb dropped on Hiroshima, Japan, in 1945.
   It was the sixth Soviet nuclear test of the year.
</TEXT>
