<1ST_LINE>r a PM-People-ChastityBono     06-14 0235</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Chastity Bono,0241</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Daughter of Sonny and Cher Likes to Keep a Low Profile</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chastity Bono, the 19-year-old daughter of Sonny
Bono and Cher, says she's a casual ``jeans and T-shirt'' kind of
person, unlike her fashion-plate mother.
   ``I was never into that from the start,'' Miss Bono says of her
mother's taste for flashy, provocative clothes.
   ``Chas,'' as she likes to be called, says in July's McCall's
magazine that living with Cher is ``never just a quiet day at home
with nobody around.''
   In contrast, she says, ``One thing I've always liked about being
at Dad's: It's always been really calm and normal. That serenity is
one thing he gave me that's really important.''
   The years after her parents divorced were difficult, Miss Bono
said.
   ``My parents weren't around a lot,'' she said. ``The divorce hit
when I was 3, and I would go back and forth between my parents'
houses _ crying for each one when I was with the other.''
   She said it took her awhile to adjust to the many companions of
both parents.
   ``It was difficult because I'd get attached to someone and
they'd leave,'' she said. ``But it didn't bother me after a while
because it was just their lives, not my life. And it isn't like
these people are coming in and trying to be my new mom and dad;
they're just friends.''
</TEXT>
