<2ND_LINE>PM-Philippines,0255</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suspected Communist Assassins Wound Policeman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Communist gunmen critically wounded a
city policeman bathing outside his home today and scattered
leaflets claiming responsibility for the attack, authorities and
witnesses said.
   It was the second rebel attack on policemen in two days in the
capital area.
   Police and witnesses said patrolman Gilbert dela Cruz was taking
a bath outside his house in a slum district when four armed men
arrived. One acted as a lookout while the others fired at dela
Cruz, police said.
   They said the anti-narcotics officer was in critical condition
in a hospital with four gunshot wounds in the head and body.
   ``We're sure that the attackers were communist rebels,'' Lt.
Loreto Idanan said.
   He said that before escaping into an ally in the crowded
neighborhood, the gunmen scattered copies of a statement
identifying themselves as members of the Alex Boncayao Brigade.
   The group is the Manila unit of the communist New People's Army.
The communists have fought a 20-year insurgency against the
national government.
   In the statement, the brigade accused dela Cruz of extortion, of
helping organize a local anti-communist vigilante group, and of
executing suspected rebel supporters.
   On Monday, two gunmen shot to death a police intelligence
officer in the Manila suburb of Pasay. Police said the gunmen also
belonged to the brigade, which has been blamed for killing at least
30 policemen and soldiers and 24 civilians in the Manila area this
year.
</TEXT>
