<1ST_LINE>r a PM-SchoolBear     06-14 0178</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-School Bear,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bear Taken From School Field After Eight-Hour Visit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WALDWICK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 200-pound black bear found lounging in a
high school field in this New York City suburb kept students in
school before being tranquilized and removed, police said.
   A mailman sighted the 6-foot-tall bear at 1:45 p.m. Monday. The
bruin later was found lingering in the fenced-in field between
Waldwick High School and a house, said police dispatcher Andrew
Sansone.
   Police were called, and hundreds of high school students were
forbidden to walk home past the area, Sansone said. The students
were held in school an extra 45 minutes until parents or others
picked them up.
   Residents threw peanut butter-and-jelly sandwiches inside the
fence for the bear as local officials awaited state Division of
Fish, Game and Wildlife officers, the dispatcher said.
   The bear was shot with a tranquilizer gun after spending several
hours up a tree, Sansone said. It was to be released to a more
remote, wooded area of the state.
   Bear sightings in Waldwick are rare, the dispatcher said.
