<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Brites     06-14 0321</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Brites,0338</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bright and Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHRISTIANSBURG, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Montgomery County residents upset
about a tax increase know where to gripe, thanks to a sign posted
in a county office listing the home telephone number of four
tax-raising supervisors.
   Treasurer Ellis Meredith posted the sign to ward off complaints.
   ``I have had an enormous number of people who come into the
office, and they direct their complaints to me as if I'm the one
who raises taxes,'' Meredith said.
   Ellis says the sign is just a source of information, but the
supervisors see it another way.
   Supervisor Todd Solberg blasted the sign as ``a misuse of a
courthouse facility, while Supervisor Ann Hess called it ``terribly
unprofessional.''
   Ms. Hess said she received calls from people who objected to the
sign, but none from tax opponents.
   Earlier this year, the supervisors voted 4-3 to approve a 16.7
percent property tax increase in this southeastern Virginia county.
   Meredith, who had opposed the increase, defended the sign.
   ``If they vote to raise taxes, then they ought to be man or
woman enough to stand up outside the board meeting and say, `I was
responsible for it,''' Meredith said.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>BREMERTON, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It was a meeting made in heaven, but the
marriage was all wet.
   Jay Adams met Cynthia Baltzelle packing parachutes for a U.S.
Army Reserve unit in Seattle. They were married Saturday under 30
feet of water.
   More than 50 guests gathered around a TV monitor on Harper Dock,
across Pugent Sound from Seattle, to watch the videotaped ceremony
and listen via an underwater sound system.
   The couple was radiant in their blue wet suits. They wore their
wedding bands on bracelets outside of their diving mittens, and
exchanged them after they surfaced.
   When it came time to kiss, they rubbed faceplates.
   The bride, a plant worker, and the groom, a truck driver,
planned a diving honeymoon in the Caribbean.
</TEXT>
