<HEAD>Cuomo: My Wife Won't Give Me Birthday Present</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gov. Mario Cuomo, about to turn 56, joked
Tuesday that his wife is so angry at him over attempts to cut
funding for a state council she runs that she's threatened not to
buy him a birthday present.
   Cuomo, facing a potential $900 million budget deficit, has
proposed cutting all sorts of spending for the current fiscal year,
including $500,000 of the $4 million budget for the Council on
Children and Families.
   ``She was very unhappy, but businesslike,'' Cuomo said. ``She
said, `Why did you do it to me?' I said, `We didn't do it to you.'''
   Cuomo said he then offered Matilda Cuomo the same deal he made
to his cabinet members and other state agency heads facing possible
budget cuts.
   ``I said, `If you can find a better cut, we'll consider it,'''
he explained. ``She said, `Good, we'll start with your birthday
present.'''
   Cuomo's birthday is Wednesday.
